Laws of Nature -- Inviolable (violations disprove the law).
Natural Law -- Elastically violable (violations corrected by the nature of being). Liberalism, when it understood itself, was grounded in this.
Positive Law -- Arbitrarily violable, and often in violation of Natural Law.
